The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                The condition of former chief minister Siddhartha Shankar Ray deteriorated on Monday and he underwent dialysis. Ray, who was admitted to a private hospital in the city on Saturday, was stable after the procedure, said officials. He is suffering from chronic renal failure.     Power supply may be disrupted in the Prince Anwar Shah Road, Jodhpur Park, Jadavpur, Golf Green, Poddar Park and South City areas between 8.30am and 9.30pm on Tuesday because of CESC maintenance work.    Air India has been operating daily flights in the Calcutta-Hyderabad-Calcutta sector to meet the rush of passengers. Till Sunday, the airline had been operating four flights a week in the sector. Air India will also increase the frequency of Calcutta-Bagdogra-Calcutta flights from thrice a week to four times.     Homemaker Ruma Ghosh, 55,was found hanging from the ceiling of her room by a sari in her Hari Sabha Street home on Monday. She was declared dead at SSKM Hospital.                                                                                                                                                  
